The tanker overturned, unleashing an inferno, early on Wednesday morning. Courtesy #DStv403 WORCESTER - A truck transporting gas bottles has exploded in Worcester in the Western Cape. The tanker overturned, unleashing an inferno early on Wednesday morning. Two firefighters were injured in the blast. READ: Authorities monitoring Algoa Bay oil spill The explosion was so big, that locals reportedly felt a tremor several kilometres away. Several streets in Worcester are closed this morning.